description.narrative: UNICEF almost doubled its outreach capacity to the benefit of out-of-school children and adolescents compared to 2018 and scaled up catch-up interventions from 2 regions initially to 7 regions this year. Significant progress was made towards addressing the specific needs of girls with the introduction of menstrual hygiene management at school, and towards children with disabilities with the formulation of a draft policy framework on inclusive education. Significant support was also provided to facilitate the development of safe, healthy, and conducive learning environments with particular focus on schools located in underserved and rural areas. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
